<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus absent. Thallus inconspicuous, endolithic. Perithecia 0.18-0.23 mm, 3/4-1-immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock; ca. 100-110 perithecia/cm2. Ostiole depressed, ca. 20-50 mm wide. Involucrellum absent (?). Exciple ca. 0.2 mm in diam., wall dark. Ascospores 0-septate, ca. 17-21 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11-12 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The studied specimen may be a tiny syntype. Nylander has annotated to the specimen: spores 18-24 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11-14 mm. 
